                <head>152. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>Fourteen draft memoranda from <persName corresp="#p_MNRS1">McNamara</persName> to
                    President <persName>Johnson</persName> are included in “Department of Defense
                    Draft Memoranda for the President: Recommended <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss>
                    1965-1969 Defense Programs,” a compendium dated December 19, 1963. The memoranda
                    at Tabs I, II, and III are printed as Documents 151, 145, and 153,
                    respectively.</p>
                <p>The remaining documents in this compendium, none printed, are: “Recommended
                        <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1965-<gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss>
                    1969 Air Force Tactical Program,” dated December 12, 1963; “Attack Carrier (CVA)
                    Forces,” dated December 18, 1963; “Anti-Submarine Warfare Forces <gloss
                        target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1965-<gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1969,”
                    dated December 11, 1963; “Recommended <gloss target="#t_FY1"
                        >FY</gloss>1965-<gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1969 Amphibious Assault
                    Forces,” dated December 10, 1963; “Naval Mine Warfare Forces,” dated December
                    11, 1963; “Recommended <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1965-<gloss
                        target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1969 Fleet Air Defense Systems,” dated December
                    19, 1963; “Navy Shipbuilding and Conversion Program,” dated December 11, 1963;
                    “Underway Replenishment Forces,” dated December 11, 1963; “Recommended <gloss
                        target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1965-<gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1969
                    Airlift and Sealift Forces,” dated December 6, 1963; “National Deep Underground
                    Command Center as a Key <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1965 Budget
                    Consideration,” November 7, 1963; and “<gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1965
                    Budget, Research and Development,” December 16, 1963. (National Archives and
                    Records Administration, <gloss target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 218, <gloss
                        target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> Records, JMF 7000 (3 Jan 64) Sec 1A)</p>
